      <div xml:id="NA186-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta tōḻikkut talaivi (ET: “āṟṟuval” eṉpatupaṭac) colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said to the confidante who had become weak in the time of separation.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA186">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kallūṟ ṟīṇṭala kayaṉaṟa vāṅki</l>
<l>            yirumpiṇart taṭakkai nīṭṭi nīrkoṇṭu</l>
<l>            peruṅkai yāṉai piṭiyeti rōṭuṅ</l>
<l>            kāṉam vempiya vaṟaṅkūr kaṭattiṭai</l>
<l>            vēṉi lōti niṟampeyar mutupōttup </l>
<l>            pāṇyāḻ kaṭaiya vāṅkip pāṅkar</l>
<l>            neṭunilai yāa mēṟun toḻila</l>
<l>            piṟarkkeṉa muyalum pērā ṇeñcamoṭu</l>
<l>            kāmar poruṭpiṇip pōkiya</l>
<l>            nāmvēṅ kātalar ceṉṟa vāṟē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent4">Full of toil [are] they,</l>
<l>the paths taken by the lover whom we are burning for,</l>
<l rend="indent">who has gone enticed by desired wealth,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with the heart of a great man that exhorts itself saying “for others”,</l>
<l rend="indent">– where the colour-changing old male of the chameleon in summer</l>
<l rend="indent">ascends the Yām tree with broad base</l>
<l rend="indent">nearby, greedily(?)<note place="foot">The meaning of <term xml:lang="ta">kaṭaiya</term> here is not at all clear; T.V.G. explains it as the playing of the Yāḻ, which is nowhere near the dictionaries. Parallels? In any case the image is elliptical: we have to surmise that some desert travellers play to themselves when taking rest.</note> taking in the melodious lute,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the midst of the wilderness fully in drought pressing hot</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the forest,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the large-trunked elephant runs towards [its] female</l>
<l rend="indent2">with water, stretching out [its] broad trunk of dark roughness,</l>
<l rend="indent2">having absorbed the gatherings from the rocky spring,</l>
<l rend="indent3">so that the pond subsides.</l>
        </lg>
